# 7. ショーという名のプレゼント

Kohane: Wow... Look at how many guests have gathered!
Toya: The staff even said this is more people than they were initially expecting.
Toya: Some apparently became interested in watching after we asked them about making lanterns with us.
Akito: Gotcha. I guess that ended up being a good way of advertising it.
An: That means we were able to help! Let's do our best when the moment comes!
Kohane: Yeah!
Staff Member: Thank you all for your patience. The Christmas show will begin momentarily!
Akito: Oh, it's starting.
Santa Claus A: “Hmph...! Hmph...!”
Santa Claus B: “You seem to be training harder than usual today. But this is our big day, so be careful not to get injured, okay?”
Santa Claus A: “Yes, I'm being careful. But I can't seem to stay still. After all, it's Christmas Eve!”
Akito: These are the Santa Clauses...?
An: Looks like it... They're wearing red suits and hats, but...
An: They all seem way too buff...!
Toya: I've never seen such burly Santa Clauses before...
Kohane: Oh, look...! The one on the right is a member of the Phoenix Stage cast!
Akito: You serious? How can you tell? His beard and hat are covering up most of his face.
An: Haha. Nothing gets by Kohane!
Santa Claus C: “Those scoundrels are likely going to test us again this year by trying to prevent us from delivering our presents. But we shall overcome...!”
Santa Claus C: “For the sake of the children!”
Santa Clauses: “Yeah!”
Santa Claus A: “Alright, we're set to take off. Let's fly, my trusty reindeer!”
Reindeer: “Yes, I'll pull my hardest again this year!”
Reindeer: “And my red nose will light up the night sky...!”
Children: Wow, his nose is actually glowing! That's really cute!
Kohane: Tsukasa and Emu are playing the reindeer...!
Toya: Yes, that suits Tsukasa very well since carrying the presents is a very important job...
Reindeer: “Alright, let's go deliver these to the children!”
Phantom Christmas Trees: “Arrrgh! M-My branch... The lights wrapped around it are so bright...!”
Reindeer: “I don't think any of us were expecting Christmas tree monsters to appear...!”
Reindeer: “But it seems that they're weak against flashing lights!”
Phantom Christmas Trees: “Grr...! How were you muscleheads able to wrap these around us so nimbly?”
Santa Claus C: “Heh. That's because the children are going to love seeing you all gussied up...”
Santa Claus C: “We're doing this for them!”
Phantom Christmas Trees: “For the children... Alas, we must admit defeat...”
Reindeer: “The trees are running...! Way to go, you guys!”
Santa Claus B: “Yes, this is why we carry around lights for different kinds of trees.”
Santa Claus A: “But many trials still lie ahead. Stay frosty, my trusty reindeer!”
Reindeer: “Roger!”
Phantom Snowman: “Wait, Santa!”
Phantom Snowman: “You shall not pass... Leave those presents and flee!”
Santa Claus B: “These presents are for the children. We are not about to let you have them.”
Phantom Snowman: “Fine. Then, we will take them from you... Pummel them with snowballs, everyone!”
Phantom Snowman: “Here comes the snowstorm!”
Children: Wow, look at all the snowballs...! This is so cool!
Santa Claus A: “Grr... So many snowballs...!”
An: H-Hey, that looks like...!
Akito: Kusanagi's backstage making all the snowballs. I know she's using that machine, but she's churning out a ton.
Reindeer: “No... I can't move forward at all...”
Santa Claus C: “Don't give up! This is when you need to curl up your fists and...!”
Santa Claus C: “Do this!”
Phantom Snowman: “What...? He's punching them to pieces?!”
Children: Cool!
Children: Go, Santa, go!!
Reindeer: “Oh, I can hear the children...!”
Santa Claus C: “Yes, so we can't afford to fail here. We must keep moving forward... For the children!”
Santa Claus C: *Roar*
Children: Go, Santa!
Kohane: They're so strong!
Toya: Yes, to think that they could punch their way through that storm of snowballs...!
Rui: (Alright... So far, so good.)
Rui: (The climax is coming up soon.)
Rui: (After the lights go out, the staff will guide the guests down the slope and light the lanterns.)
Rui: (We'll all need to work together in unison, but I'm sure...)
Santa Claus A: “Oh, I'm starting to see some lights! We must be approaching the city!”
Santa Claus A: “This is it, trusty reindeer! The home stretch!”
Reindeer: “...”
Santa Claus B: “What's wrong? Why have you stopped? Your nose has even gone out.”
Santa Claus A: “Huh...?! The city's lights just all went out...!”
Santa Claus C: “Wh-What's going on?! We won't be able to see where all the houses are... That means it's going to be impossible to deliver these presents!”
Reindeer: “He...”
Reindeer: “Hehehe... Hahahahaha!”
Santa Claus B: “What's so funny?”
Reindeer: “You really are muscleheads! It was so obvious that you wouldn't be able to find the children's houses if all the lights went out!”
Santa Claus A: “No, you didn't...!”
Reindeer: “Hehehe... Delivering those presents is going to be impossible now. So, hand them over!”
Santa Claus B: “Grr... We were so close...!”
Toya: The lights have gone out... This is the signal to take our lanterns down.
Staff Member: Alright, everyone, please start making your way down the slope!
Children: Okay!
Staff Member: Please form a single-file line. Also, it's very dark, so please watch your step.
Kohane: (Despite having to make a drastic change, everyone's moving along like this was the original plan...)
Kohane: (People who make shows really are amazing...!)
Audience: Hehe. I'm getting kinda nervous...
Audience: You got your lantern?
Audience: Yeah! This is so exciting...!
Rui: (Okay, it looks like everybody is in position. All that's left is to...)
Reindeer: “Hand over the presents already! Honestly, what's the point of holding on to them?”
Reindeer: “It's not like they're going to reach their recipients now!”
Santa Claus A: “But... But! We have to deliver these...!”
Staff Member: That's our signal! One, two!
Santa Claus B: “Hey, look towards the city...!”
Santa Claus C: “There's a path! Made of light!”
Children: Wh-Whoa...! It's so pretty!
Reindeer: “No! None of the lights should be working... Who's behind this?!”
Locals: “Santa! Over here!”
Santa Claus C: “Those are the locals... They're using lanterns to indicate where their houses are!”
Santa Claus B: “They're trying to help us.”
Santa Claus A: “Let's go! We need to get these presents to the children!”
Kohane: Oh, they're skiing towards us...!
Reindeer: “S-Stop! Those presents belong to us...!”
Santa Claus C: “Hah hah hah hah! You'll never catch us! Not with those puny legs!”
Akito: They're acting while skiing...?
Kohane: Yeah, that's amazing...!
Santa Claus A: “The wait is over! And thank you all for your help! We have your presents right here!”
Children: Wow...! It's really Santa Claus! This is amazing...
Santa Claus C: “We can feel your collective desire to see us from all the way across the sky.”
Santa Claus C: “So, thank you for believing in us.”
Children: Santa...
Children: Wow... They really heard our wishes...!
Children: Um, Santa... Will we get to see you again?
Santa Claus C: “Yes, next year... I promise to return no matter what.”
Santa Claus C: “So, until then, be very good!”
Children: We will...!
